Reviews.Title: Great Laptop
Reviews.Author: E. H.
Reviews.Content: Wow is one way of putting my thoughts after opening the box to power up this laptop. Its great and the screen size is huge. Fast and easy to operate. Shipping was quick and delivery was no hassle at all. Check out this product for the latest and best. Great buy I think. Enjoy yours because I know I will certainly make good use of mine!

Reviews.Title: Great cost/benefit
Reviews.Author: Nivaldo Jose Simas
Reviews.Content: It performs according to my expectation and has an excelent cost/benefit...It is a nice option when you enter on the high performance pc world....

Reviews.Title: Very nice computer
Reviews.Author: William Bastian
Reviews.Content: Very nice computer, fast. so far no glitches.  Just waiting for Windows 8.1, so I can get rid of Windows 8 which sucks.

Reviews.Title: This product came out really cool
Reviews.Author: jjunior
Reviews.Content: the product is presented in its original packaging and respecting the rules of sending apparatus of its kind and not to mention the quality, came fenomenalm, very good product

Reviews.Title: nice big computer
Reviews.Author: zemator
Reviews.Content: Arrived quickly and is working great.  Windows 8 doesn't seem to be a problem.  I was able to get it to work without many issues.

Reviews.Title: Dont buy Dell from a local vendor
Reviews.Author: Karn
Reviews.Content: this laptop arrived broken. it was dysfunctional and did not even turn on. and since i took the laptop to India, they refused to fix it there. i asked them to fix it coz it was damaged even before turning on, but they refused to fix it in India and asked to bring it back to USA.i then went to the Dell center, and surprisingly, they refused to do it to. i do get why dell wouldn't do it. i didnt have international warranty and i didnt even buy it from the dell store.be careful while buying from local vendors.

Reviews.Title: Great Laptop for most uses
Reviews.Author: average joe
Reviews.Content: Purchased this laptop for my son for college.  Very pleased with the price and he is happy with the performance.  It does come with Windows 8, which has taken him some time to get used to, but it's not that bad once you do.  Laptop is good quality.  He's had it a couple months now and hasn't had any issues with it.  It's a powerful machine--he uses for gaming as well as other purposes, and all his games have done just fine with it.  My only complaint is that I somehow that all Dell i17R laptops came with a slot for a second hard drive.  Apparently only some do.  I had planned to install a SSD in a second bay and put Windows 7 on it, to get an even faster machine, using the 1TB for game data, music, videos, etc., but that is not an option.  Overall, very pleased though.

Reviews.Title: eh
Reviews.Author: David Jozef Tozier
Reviews.Content: The info and gear this thing comes with make it seem amazing, but for some reason it is slow.  Another problem is getting the two video cards to even work properly in tandem, or getting some games to start up at all.  Maybe I'm having driver problems, but I've had it for a while and it has given me a lot of guff, kinda a headache.

Reviews.Title: Very good computer! ! !
Reviews.Author: ion
Reviews.Content: This computer is sleek & light. With an i7 core, it is very fast! It turns on quickly. It is also a master at multi-tasking, and barely lags. . . Overall, I am very happy with this purchase!

Reviews.Title: Get A Mac!!!!
Reviews.Author: Exvegman
Reviews.Content: After owning this computer for 6 months, it crashed and would not boot. I fortunately had purchased an extended warranty and Dell sent a technician (160 mi round trip) to replace the motherboard. The computer worked fine for 2 days then crashed again. Dell again sent a technician who again replaced the motherboard. Shortly after, the keyboard stopped working, so for the third time Dell is sending a technician to make a Band Aid fix to this lemon. In total, I have been required to use 12 hours vacation time and have spent no less than 5 hours on the phone with Dell technicians. I would recommend a Commodore 64 over this POS.
